---
import type { CollectionEntry } from "astro:content";
import ArtistCard from "./ArtistCard.astro";
import Tooltip from "./Tooltip.astro";
import Separator from "../components/Separator.astro";

type Props = {
  artists: CollectionEntry<"artists">[];
};

const { artists } = Astro.props;
const grid = "artists";
---
<p>I've been localizing games across multiple platforms for over five years, and I've been a gamer since I could hold a controller.</p>
<p>My journey has shown me that video games are one of the most intricate art forms of our time, which is why I'm deeply committed to <b>creating seamless experiences</b> for players worldwide, ensuring that every element of your game is <b>meticulously localized</b> to resonate with its audience.</p>

<Separator />

<h2>What I do</h2>

<ul class="pills">
  <li>Translation</li>
  <li>Adaptation</li>
  <li>Glossary Creation</li>
  <li>Localization</li>
  <li>Transcreation</li>
  <li>Editing</li>
  <li>Proofreading</li>
  <li>LQA</li>
</ul>

<ul class="services-grid">
  <li>
    <span>
      <img src="/src/assets/images/gamer.gif" alt="">
      <h3>Gamer Vision</h3>
    </span>
    <p>Gamers don't settle for mediocrityâ€”they recognize quality instantly. A well-designed game speaks to its audience and respects cultural and linguistic expectations. I bring the gamer's perspective your localization needs to truly succeed.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <span>
      <img src="/src/assets/images/devices.gif" alt="">
      <h3>PC, Consoles &amp; Mobile</h3>
    </span>
    <p>Years in the industry have given me a solid command of the terminology for every gaming platform.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <span>
      <img src="/src/assets/images/portatil.gif" alt="">
      <h3>Glossary Creation</h3>
    </span>
    <p>I create glossaries and termbases from scratch to streamline your game's localization and minimize errors.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <span>
      <img src="/src/assets/images/translator.gif" alt="">
      <h3>Adaptation</h3>
    </span>
    <p>If your game is already localized into ESES (Spanish for Spain), I can adapt it to ESLA (Spanish for Latin America) to effectively reach your Latin American audience.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <span>
      <img src="/src/assets/images/recibo.gif" alt="">
      <h3>CATs</h3>
    </span>
    <p>I work with MemoQ, Phrase, SmartCat, and many more.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<Separator />

<h2>Recent projects</h2>
<p>While much of my work is confidential due to non-disclosure agreements, I'm proud to share a selection of <b>credited</b> projects below.</p>
<section class="artist-grid" id="grid" data-grid={grid}>
  {artists.map((artist) => <ArtistCard artist={artist} />)}
</section>

